{{Use dmy dates|date=July 2017}} {{Infobox person | name = Lee Man Tat | image = | image_size = | caption = | birth_name = | birth_date = {{bya|1929}} | birth_place = [[Macau]] (now part of China) | death_date = | death_place = | death_cause = | nationality = Hong Kong | residence = Hong Kong | education = | alma mater = | occupation = Businessman | title = Chairman, [[Lee Kum Kee]] | term = | predecessor = | successor = | known for = | boards = | salary = | networth = US$11.6 billion (2018)<ref name="forbes1">{{cite web|url=https://www.forbes.com/profile/lee-man-tat/ |title=Lee Man Tat |publisher=Forbes.com |accessdate=27 July 2017}}</ref> | spouse = married | children = 5 | parents = [[Lee Siu-nam]] | relations = [[Lee Kum-sheung]] (grandfather) | website = }}
'''Lee Man Tat''' [[Bronze Bauhinia Star|BBS]] (born 1929) is a Hong Kong [[billionaire]], the chairman of the family-owned Chinese sauce and condiment company [[Lee Kum Kee]].<ref name="forbes1"/> His wealth is estimated at $11.6bn, according to Forbes and in July 2017 the group purchased London's landmark Walkie-Talkie skyscraper.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.theguardian.com/money/2017/jul/27/londons-walkie-talkie-building-sold-for-record-breaking-13bn|title=London's Walkie Talkie building sold for record-breaking £1.3bn|last=Butler|first=Sarah|date=2017-07-27|work=The Guardian|access-date=2017-08-03|language=en-GB|issn=0261-3077}}</ref>
==Early life== Lee Man Tat was born in [[Macau]] in 1929.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://ourhkfoundation.org.hk/en/node/942 |title=Mr. Lee Man Tat &#124; Our Hong Kong Foundation |publisher=Ourhkfoundation.org.hk |date= |accessdate=27 July 2017}}</ref> He is the eldest son of [[Lee Siu-nam]], who was the third son of [[Lee Kum-sheung]], who founded the company and invented [[oyster sauce]] in [[Zhuhai]] in 1888.<ref name="ejinsight1">{{cite web|url=http://www.ejinsight.com/20161116-lee-kum-kee-the-family-grows-and-stays-together/ |title=Lee Kum Kee: The family grows and stays together |publisher=Ejinsight.com |date=16 November 2016 |accessdate=27 July 2017}}</ref>
==Career== Lee joined [[Lee Kum Kee]] and took over the running of the company from his father in 1972, when he bought out his uncles with the help of his father.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://ourhkfoundation.org.hk/en/node/942 |title=Mr. Lee Man Tat &#124; Our Hong Kong Foundation |publisher=Ourhkfoundation.org.hk |date= |accessdate=27 July 2017}}</ref><ref name="ejinsight1"/> In 1986, he bought his younger brother's 40% stake.<ref name="ejinsight1"/>
==Personal life== Lee is married, with five children, and lives in Hong Kong.<ref name="forbes1"/> His eldest son, [[Lee Wai-chung]], joined the business in 1985.<ref name="ejinsight1"/>
