{{Use dmy dates|date=July 2017}} {{Infobox person | name = Luigi Cremonini | image = | image_size = | caption = | birth_name = | birth_date = {{birth year and age|1939}} | birth_place = | death_date = | death_place = | death_cause = | nationality = Italian | residence = [[Modena]], Italy | education = | alma mater = | occupation = businessman | title = | term = | predecessor = | successor = | known for = | boards = | salary = | networth = US$1.8 billion (August 2018)<ref name="forbes1">{{cite web|url=https://www.forbes.com/profile/luigi-cremonini/ |title=Luigi Cremonini & family |publisher=Forbes.com |accessdate=24 July 2017}}</ref> | spouse = married | children = 4 | parents = | relations = | website = }} '''Luigi Cremonini''' (born 1939) is an Italian [[billionaire]] businessman. He is the chairman of Cremonini SpA and Inalca SpA, and the honorary president of the Chamber of Commerce ItalAfrica Centrale.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.cremonini.com/en/gruppo/management|title=The management of the Cremonini Group|website=www.cremonini.com|access-date=2018-08-21}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.italafricacentrale.com/index.php?option=com_content&view=article&id=131&Itemid=35&lang=en|title=Directive Council|last=Marco|website=www.italafricacentrale.com|language=en-gb|access-date=2018-08-21}}</ref>
==Early life== Cremonini was born in 1939,<ref name="fundinguniverse1">{{cite web|url=http://www.fundinguniverse.com/company-histories/cremonini-s-p-a-history/ |title=History of Cremonini S.p.A. – FundingUniverse |publisher=Fundinguniverse.com |date= |accessdate=24 July 2017}}</ref> into a poor farming family near [[Modena]], Italy.<ref name="forbes1"/> He studied farming in Bologna.<ref name="fundinguniverse1"/> In May 1994, the University of Bologna awarded him the honorary degree in veterinary medicine.{{fact|date=August 2018}}
==Career== In 1963, Cremonini opened, with his brother Giuseppe a small butcher's shop, the start of the pan-European Cremonini Group, with an annual turnover of meat products of $3.6 billion, and Marr, Italy's largest food-service distributor.<ref name="forbes1"/>
==Personal life== Cremonini is married, with four children, and lives in [[Modena]], Italy.<ref name="forbes1"/>
In 1985, he was awarded the [[Order of Orange-Nassau]] by the [[Beatrix of the Netherlands|Queen Beatrix]] and appointed [[Order of Merit for Labour|Cavalier of Labour]] by the President [[Sandro Pertini|Alessandro Pertini]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.economiaitaliana.it/it/articolo.php/Luigi-Cremonini-politica-e-burocrazia-hanno-avvelenato-la-voglia-di-creare-imprese?LT=IMPRE&ID=11665&ARCHIVIO=1|title=Economia Italiana: articoli, interviste, news di economia - Luigi Cremonini: politica e burocrazia hanno avvelenato la voglia di creare imprese|website=www.economiaitaliana.it|access-date=2018-08-21}}</ref> In October 2009, Cremonini was presented with an "Italy in the World 2009" award at the Italian Embassy in Moscow.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.italafricacentrale.com/index.php?option=com_content&view=article&id=124:assegnato-a-luigi-cremonini-il-qpremio-italia-nel-mondo-2009q&catid=12:eventi&Itemid=500223&lang=en|title=The "Award Italy in the World 2009" assigned to Luigi Cremonini|last=Mariarosaria|website=www.italafricacentrale.com|language=en-gb|access-date=2018-08-21}}</ref>
